V. Myogenesis
	A. Myogenic factors-Myf5 and MyoD-TTYP on Monday
		1. Expression of myoD or myf5 in tissue culture
			 cells results in a muscle cell phenotype.
		2. Homozygous myoD knockout mice form muscle.
		3. Homozygous myf5 knockout mice form muscle.
		4. Homozygous myoD and myf5 double mutant knockout
			 mice do not form muscle.
	B. How to produce a multinucleate cell?-TTYP on Monday
		1. Beginning with a population of myoblasts,
			 how could a multinucleate myotube be
			 obtained?
		2. Evidence using isocitrate dehydrogenase-Mintz
			 and Baker 1967

